  , issueCommentBody =
      "Suppose I want to add some sort of ordering to my documents, I could do the following:\r\n\r\n    for_each(zip(table.sort(...), range()), \r\n        lambda x: table.get(x[0][\"id\"]).update({\"ordering\" : x[1]}))\r\n\r\nThis adds a field to each document called ordering such that each document has a unique value and the values are dense.\r\n\r\n(Note I'm using an unproposed version of range here `range()` which is the infinite range starting at 0 (0,1,2 ...).\r\n\r\nEdit: readability of code."
